Student leaders from various institutions have today pledged their support for Baringo senator and KANU national chairman Gideon Moi in his bid to become the country&rsquo;s president. Speaking after they met him at his Kabarak home, the student leaders expressed their faith in Gideon&rsquo;s leadership stating that it will directly be of benefit to them. They also spoke about their hope for a united country, expressing confidence that the BBI will be back to achieve national unity. On his part, the KANU chairman implored upon the students to individually take charge of political activities in order to attain gainful leadership.